Information about the used dataset¶

For this task a data set is taken into account of engine boat sell offers in Europe + Swizerland and some other countries from a marketing team. The data set includes 10 categories: Price, Boat Type, Manufacturer, Type, Year Built, Length, Width, Material, Location and Number of views last 7 days. This is a good starting point for investigating the most favoured boats on the lake of constance ant where to buy them the cheapest in Europe.The Source of data is: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/karthikbhandary2/boat-sales?resource=download

The dataset does not take sailing yachts into account.

# Data preparation
# Investigation how the "Bodensee, Lake of Constance is spelled in the data set"

unique_locations = boat_data['Location'].unique().tolist()
print(len(unique_locations))
#print(unique_locations)

#Lake Constance
#Konstanz
#Constance 
#Bodensee

# Replace multiple spelling of the Lake Constance by "Bodensee"
boat_data_cleaned = boat_data.copy()

# List of names to replace by "Bodensee"
terms_to_replace = ['Lake Constance', 'Konstanz', 'Constance', 'Bodensee', 'bodensee','lake constance', 'konstanz', 'constance',]

# Define function to replace listed values by a new one
def replace_location(location):
    if isinstance(location, str):  # Is string?
        for term in terms_to_replace:
            if term in location:
                return 'Bodensee'
    return location

#Define function to shorten the locations to countries and copy the remaining location into a new column location area
def split_location(location):
    if isinstance(location, str):  # Is string?
        parts = location.split(' ', 1)  # Split at the first whitespace
        if len(parts) > 1:
            return pd.Series([parts[0], parts[1]])
        else:
            return pd.Series([parts[0], np.nan])
    return pd.Series([location, np.nan])

#Recalculate all boat prices into €

# Exchange rate table
exchange_rates = {
    'CHF': 0.92,  # 1 CHF = 0.92 EUR
    'DKK': 0.13,  # 1 DKK = 0.13 EUR
    'EUR': 1.0    # EUR stays unchanged
}

# function for calculation
def convert_to_euro(price):
    if isinstance(price, str):
        currency, amount = price.split(' ', 1)
        amount = float(amount.replace(',', '').replace('.', ''))
        if currency in exchange_rates:
            return amount * exchange_rates[currency]
    return np.nan

# Remove nan and 0 values
def remove_zero_or_nan_rows(df):
    cleaned_df = df.replace(0, np.nan)  # Entfernt Zeilen mit 0 Einträgen
    cleaned_df = df.dropna()  # Entfernt Zeilen mit NaN in 'Year Built'
    
    return cleaned_df


# Apply functions

#Replace by Bodensee
boat_data_cleaned['Location'] = boat_data_cleaned['Location'].apply(replace_location)
unique_locations_cleaned = boat_data_cleaned['Location'].unique().tolist()
print(len(unique_locations_cleaned))

# Umrechnung der Preise
boat_data_cleaned['Price (EUR)'] = boat_data_cleaned['Price'].apply(convert_to_euro)
boat_data_cleaned.drop(columns=['Price'], inplace=True)

# Remove 0 and none rows
#boat_data_cleaned = remove_zero_or_nan_rows(boat_data_cleaned)

boat_data_cleaned_countries_splitted = boat_data_cleaned.copy()
boat_data_cleaned_countries_splitted[['Location', 'Location Area']] = boat_data_cleaned_countries_splitted['Location'].apply(split_location)

#store to csv

Result of Data preparation¶

  • Multiple namings for lake of constance are replaced by Bodensee
  • A new feature is created out of the original location feature. The new location contains the country of boat sell and the additional Location Area contains further information regarding the place in the country.
  • The boat prices are recalculated in €.
  • The data is plotted by distribution of boats to sell in the different countries.

We now have a good representative where we can further build the analysis on where we can buy the most popular boat for the Bodensee at the best price. Our data frame contains numerical as well as categorical features which needs to be interpreted seperatly in the following anlysis part.

# Filter boats by boat type
def filter_boat(df, BoatType):
    return df[df['Boat Type'] == BoatType]

# Clean the years where the boats are build, since in there are 0 or nan values which falsifies the average build year. 
def clean_year_built_data(df):
    df_cleaned = df.dropna(subset=['Year Built'])  # Entfernt NaN-Werte
    df_cleaned = df_cleaned[df_cleaned['Year Built'] != 0]  # Entfernt 0-Wert
    return df_cleaned

#Plot the average year of build for the top three boats by category in Germany.
filtered_boats_germany_cleaned = clean_year_built_data(filter_boat(boats_germany, "Motor Yacht"))
average_year_built = filtered_boats_germany_cleaned['Year Built'].mean()
print(f"The average year build for Motor Yacht in Germany is: {average_year_built}")

filtered_boats_germany_cleaned = clean_year_built_data(filter_boat(boats_germany,'Sport Boat'))
average_year_built = filtered_boats_germany_cleaned['Year Built'].mean()
print(f"The average year build for Sport Boats in Germany is: {average_year_built}")

filtered_boats_germany_cleaned = clean_year_built_data(filter_boat(boats_germany, 'Cabin Boat'))
average_year_built = filtered_boats_germany_cleaned['Year Built'].mean()
print(f"The average year build for Cabin Boat in Germany is: {average_year_built}")

The most offered boat types in Germany by engine boats are Motor Yachts, Sport Boats and Cabin Boats. The same result appeares for the most viewed boats in the last 7 days in Germany. Therefore it can be stated that, the intereset in Germany is largest for these types of boats.

A Motor Yacht has the average specifications:

  • ~3.5 m width
  • ~11.5 m long
  • Used diesel engine boat
  • is build out of plastic based GRP material
  • build by Jeanneau power Boats
  • price ~250k€
  • build 2003

A Sport Boat has the average specifications:

  • ~2.48 m width
  • ~7 m long
  • New boat from stock unleaded fuel
  • is build out of plastic based GRP material
  • build by Sea Ray power boats
  • price ~50k€
  • build 2014

A Cabine Boat has the average specifications:

  • ~2.6 m width
  • ~7.8 m long
  • New boat from stock unleaded fuel
  • is build out of plastic based GRP material
  • build by Quicksilver Power Boats
  • price ~50k€
  • build 2004

The people who are thinking about buying a boat at the Bodensee (lake of constance) are most interested in a Sport Boat since there are the most views on advertisment for boat sales in the last 7 days. Fun fact is that at the same time this boat type are also available for sale most often. From my private experience of boat driving at the Bodensee (lake of constance) I can confirm that sport boats are the most popular boat types besides sailing boats at the Bodensse (lake of constance).

The most popular engine boats for the Bodensee can be bought at the lowest price in Rheinland-Pfalz and Nordrhein-Westfalen. Important to state is that there are spcial regulations regarding emissions and grey water for boats at the Bodensee (lake of constance). This can lead to further investments to get a boat licensed for the lake of constance. This furhter costs could not taken into account in this data set because there are no such information in the data set about the boats.
